<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Sol Plaatje Municipality claims the cuts were caused by upgrades being done to pipelines in the area.It’s believed a JoJo tank was moved to the area but after it was empty, residents lost patience and took to the streets.One resident said: “Sol Plaatje officials left us high and dry. “They promised us there would be other alternatives to access water but they never delivered. “It’s been four days without water in our kasi. “How do they expect us to live without water. “We will keep on protesting until our demands are met.”The resident said last week an official from the municipality had told them the matter would be resolved within three days. “We understand that upgrades need to happen but they should have provided us with enough water to get by on,” said the resident.Municipal spokesman Sello Matsie said the problem was under control.“We heard many announcements through radio stations and newspapers informing residents to store enough water during our pipeline upgrades. He said the upgrades are complete and residents would have water soon. “Because of how the water travels at this stage I cannot give the exact time when it will be available. “We would like to appeal to the residents affected to be patient,” said Matsie.